  <mainDescription>A Role defining permissions in the context of a zone, and particular object within the zone. For a given business object, a&#xD;
contextual role can be granted directly to a user or associated with one of its functional roles. Some examples of&#xD;
contextual roles are &lt;em>Administering&lt;/em>, &lt;em>Auditing&lt;/em>, &lt;em>Authoring&lt;/em>, &lt;em>Collaborating&lt;/em>, and&#xD;
&lt;em>Monitoring&lt;/em>. They are defined as a &lt;em>verb&lt;/em> within UAM, &lt;em>Ordering&lt;/em> for example. Also see definitions&#xD;
for: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_role_F41637E3.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_4cjbMOPNEdy7f9KmjDtwsA&quot;>Role&lt;/a>, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_func-role_668447D2.html&quot; guid=&quot;_8Uq7sPvGEeOyDIZvZjuaLg&quot;>Functional&#xD;
Role&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_business_activity_7539B7D1.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_qiJqEMI6EeKSedlRPHdUIQ&quot;>Business Activity&lt;/a>. &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In order to avoid confusion between functional roles and contextual roles the following conventions have been adopted:&#xD;
    Functional and organizational roles will always be expressed as nouns (e.g. &lt;em>TigerTeam&lt;/em>); Contextual roles will&#xD;
    always be expressed as verbs (e.g. &lt;em>Collaborating&lt;/em>). This rule reflects the core differences between the role&#xD;
    types: functional (and organizational) roles really do refer to persons, places, or things; contextual roles are&#xD;
    actions performed by a subject on an object.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Roles are used as the fundamental method for defining access permissions to protected objects (i.e. RBAC, see: &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Role-based_access_control&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Role-Based Access Control&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;on&#xD;
    Wikipedia).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
